cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use EpiBranch.jl, please cite it as below."
title: "EpiBranch.jl: A composable branching-process engine for epidemiology"
abstract: >-
  A Julia engine for branching-process models in epidemiology, combining
  stochastic simulation with analytical inference. It brings together the
  branching-process cores of the R packages simulist, epichains and ringbp, the
  analytical superspreading methods of superspreading, and the post-exposure
  prophylaxis model of pepbp.
type: software
authors:
